@startuml Multi-Agent Orchestration - LangGraph Supervisor Pattern
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam linetype ortho

title Healthcare Insurance Multi-Agent AI Platform\nLangGraph Supervisor Orchestration Pattern\n(Prior Authorization Workflow)

rectangle "START" as START #E8F5E9
rectangle "Intake Agent" as INTAKE #E3F2FD
rectangle "Eligibility Agent" as ELIGIBILITY #FFF3E0
rectangle "Benefits Agent" as BENEFITS #FCE4EC
rectangle "Parallel Review\n(Clinical + Policy + Fraud)" as PARALLEL #F3E5F5
rectangle "Decision Agent" as DECISION #FFEBEE
rectangle "HITL Review" as HITL #FFF9C4
rectangle "Notification Agent" as NOTIFY #E1F5FE
rectangle "END" as END #C8E6C9

START --> INTAKE : app.ainvoke(PARequest)
INTAKE --> ELIGIBILITY : intake_complete
ELIGIBILITY --> BENEFITS : eligible
ELIGIBILITY --> END : not_eligible
BENEFITS --> PARALLEL : covered
BENEFITS --> END : not_covered
PARALLEL --> DECISION : merge_results
DECISION --> NOTIFY : confidence >= 0.85
DECISION --> HITL : confidence < 0.85
HITL --> NOTIFY : reviewer_completed
NOTIFY --> END

note right of INTAKE
  Intake processing
  - document classification
  - OCR extraction
  - entity extraction
  - validation
end note

note right of ELIGIBILITY
  Eligibility checks
  - active member status
  - coverage date validation
  - COB checks
end note

note right of PARALLEL
  Parallel execution block
  - clinical review with RAG
  - policy compliance checks
  - fraud risk scoring
end note

note right of DECISION
  Decision routing
  - approve or deny when confident
  - send to HITL when low confidence
end note

rectangle "Shared PAState" as STATE #E0F2F1 {
}

STATE .. INTAKE
STATE .. ELIGIBILITY
STATE .. BENEFITS
STATE .. PARALLEL
STATE .. DECISION
STATE .. HITL
STATE .. NOTIFY

note bottom of STATE
  Shared state keys
  - request and case_id
  - intake, eligibility, benefits outputs
  - clinical, policy, fraud outputs
  - decision and optional HITL result
  - append-only messages for audit trail
end note

legend bottom right
  Workflow profile
  - throughput: 50,000 workflows/day
  - simple: 2-3 min
  - standard: 5-8 min
  - complex: 15-30 min
  - SLA: 30 min with checkpointing
endlegend

@enduml
